postcontent:
Arguably the finest production non-1911 (and I am a huge Sig fan, IMHO this has a better trigger than my P227 EQ with SRT and action job - which cost me an additional $260!).  It has the O-ring barrel for greater accuracy and a recoil reduction system, which also provides more control over the Sig.  To be clear, this is the NEW Heckler & Koch version of the full-size .45 acp, about 300 rounds through the pipe, cleaned and lubed after each of about four or five uses. It is in a nice shade of FDE and is the DA/SA version and can be converted to LEM. Two 10 round mags included, along with extra back strap, box and papers. Nothing whatsoever wrong with this piece, just decided to thin the herd a bit.  It's actually a really cool gun!  Full FDE is kinda unique, too.  PRICE IS FIRM, CASH, NO TRADES - thanks.  I can do FFL to FFL shipping to conus for $45, insured.  Anyhow, keep reading if you have the cash to buy.  Also, all laws followed, i.e. 72 hr. wait from time an intent to purchase is made, ISP FOID check. Thanks

Here is what HK has to say:

The HK45 was developed as a product improvement of the highly regarded USP45, first released in the 1995. The Caliber .45 ACP HK45 includes several user-inspired enhancements including changeable grip panels (backstraps), a Picatinny MIL-STD-1913 accessory rail, better ergonomics, and more ambidextrous controls.

Along with the HK45 Compact, the HK45 was developed as a possible candidate for the Joint Combat Pistol (JCP) and Combat Pistol (CP) programs administered by the U.S. military in their search for a new service handgun to replace the 9-millimeter M9. These programs were suspended before completion and no pistols were selected.

The HK45 uses an HK proprietary O-ring barrel for precise barrel-to-slide lockup and optimal accuracy. HK45 barrels are made using the famous HK cold-hammer forging process for superior performance.

Using HK’s unique internal mechanical recoil reduction system reduces the recoil forces imparted to the weapon and shooter by as much as 30%, improving shooter control during rapid firing and increasing component service life. Capable of firing standard .45 ACP ball through +P ammunition, the HK45 combines the accuracy, modularity, reliability and minimum 20,000 round service life of the famed USP45 series with the improved ergonomics of the P2000 series pistols. HK45 models can be also be fitted with threaded barrels for use with muzzle mounted sound suppressors.

Each HK45 comes standard with an extra backstrap; medium and small interchangeable backstraps ensure an optimal fit for most shooter’s hands and complement the ergonomic profile grip.

An improved USP-style control lever, a combination safety and decocking lever, is frame mounted on the HK45 and is quickly accessible. The HK45 control lever has a positive stop and returns to the “fire” position after decocking.

By using the modular approach to the internal components first pioneered by HK on the USP, the control lever function of the HK45 can be switched from the left to the right side of the pistol to accommodate left-handed shooters (additional parts required). Left and right mounted control levers provide safety and/or decocking functions as required and can be fitted to the pistol simply by changing parts. For true ambidextrous use, a control lever can also be mounted on both sides of the pistol if required.

Well-suited for personal defense use, the HK45 is available in, or can be converted to, a wide variety of variants that use different trigger firing modes, including double action/single action (DA/SA) and DAO (double action only). The DAO mode uses the unique Heckler & Koch LEM (Law Enforcement Modification) firing system for improved double action trigger pull.

title: For Sale:  .223 or 5.56 ammo for $7.50/box CHEAP
postcontent:
I have 1,100 rounds of .223/5.56 ammo, in 55 twenty round boxes. It was all purchased from Cabela's or Palmetto State. I have Federal American Eagle .223, Federal 5.56 M193, Independence 5.56, and PMC Bronze .223 - all are FMJ 55gr.

I stocked up on range ammo awhile back, and now I'm shooting more match grade ammo for longer range target shooting. Don't need to get rid of this stuff, just figured if I could unload it, I can buy more match ammo. I paid $8-10/box for this stuff - a common price at Cabela's or Palmetto State, plus tax/shipping.

I am asking for $7.50/box, that said I would prefer to not sell less than 10 boxes at a time, as it wouldn't really be worth my time. 

So 10 boxes, 200 rounds, $75, do the math (and please search this site, Cabela's, anywhere else - you'll realize this is a great deal).

If someone wanted to buy the all of it, 1,100, I'd let it go for $400 (that's under 37 cents a round). 

Again, there's nothing wrong with this ammo, just not match grade which is what I am mostly shooting these days. If you're familiar with match ammo it isn't cheap so to feed that hobby I figured I would see if I could unload some of this range ammo.

In all honestly, I have shot about 1.5" groups at 100 yards out of my 1:7 twist AR with each of the 4 types of ammo, however, each one does shoot slightly different. So that comes into play for me shooting longer range targets as well, 4 types of ammo is a pain. But for practice, plinking, or Zombie Apocalypses this stuff should do great. Again, search around, you'll be hard pressed to beat the price.

For those who care the 1,100 is roughly:
360 Federal American Eagle .223
360 Fedeal 5.56 M193
240 Indepence 5.56
140 PMC Bronze .223
Not exact on that, if you want to know and are serious I will let you know.


$75 for 10 boxes 200 rounds
$400 for 55 boxes 1,100 rounds

postcontent: This rifle was built by red hawk custom shop in Colorado. It is a Remington 700 action with a 26" bull barrel cambered in 7mm-08. The 7mm-08 is a cartridge born from the 308 necked down to .284. There are a few great advantages to this the bullets used will have a higher BC( ballistic coefficient ). Which means the bullet flies farther, straighter, truer, greater velocity, high energy, and less recoil. It is ballistically far superior to the .308. I was able to shoot 3/4 moa with un-tuned loads very easily this is a 1/2 moa gun at 100 yards easily. It is set in a bell and Carlson A5 completely adjustable stock comb height, length of pull, and cant. Red hawk also installed a badger ordinance enlarged bolt knob, a talley 20 moa picatinny scope mount, lapped the bolt lugs, and tuned the trigger. This action is slick has been well taken care has only had 200 down the pipe. It comes with 1lb of imr4350, 40 rds of ammo, a set of RCBS dies, and assorted bullets
